metadata.name: Protein Pelt #332
metadata.description:
An incorrectly placed decimal point led to this pattern. A good friend told me it reminded them of protein structures, I found them to look like animal pelts strewn about.

Each "protein" is made up of 100 pelts, random walking around the canvas from the center. Each "pelt" is made of 5 colors sampled from an array of 84 colors.

Press 's' when in live view to save the image.

metadata.name: Sugar & Splice #339
metadata.description:
'Sugar & Splice'

Vibrant somethings, full of flavor, dancing within conjoined boundaries.

Controls:
s: Saves an image of the canvas with the current settings
1-6: Scales the canvas size, from 1 (default, 2048px x 2792px) to 6 (12288px x  16752px)
g: Toggles grain texture
t: Toggles background transparency
f: Toggles fit to screen (layout and other factors will change based on the new size, but overall style, colors, etc will remain the same)
p: Shortcut for large print settings: disables the grain texture and scales the canvas to the largest setting
b: Toggles b-side

metadata.name: Tumble Down Light Factory #416
metadata.description:
Tumble Down Light Factory is an interpretation of light installations & murals.

It attempts to trigger the feeling of coming up on a new block in a new city to discover an unexpected piece of art that is stories tall or entering a new room, knowing there will be a projection dominating the space with its light and color.

This is an abstract distillation of those things and those feelings.

Each composition is initially drawn to a hidden “template” canvas which is sampled and then rendered on the main canvas in various ways after applying some transforms to give it some depth (and so you can actually see it.)

Viewing in full-screen is nice. You should try it.

T : Save hidden ‘template’ image
S : Save current resolution
1 -> 5 : Save low -> high resolution

metadata.name: Entangled #88
metadata.description:
Entangled is a cross-chain, generative art project developed as a series of particle simulations that interact with each other in various ways across separate blockchains and browser windows. Inspired by the phenomenon of quantum entanglement, this project aims to connect two, often separate, parts of the generative art community by directly linking them together.
 
Entangled features two distinct on-chain NFT collections residing on the Ethereum and Tezos blockchains. These collections are connected through shared interactions in real-time, using cross-chain and local storage technologies to enable a system whereby particles in separate browser instances respond to and mirror each other.

The series consist of a total of 512 unique editions (256 on each blockchain) that are randomly paired with a corresponding iteration on the other. When two or more instances are opened in separate browser windows they will start to interact in different ways depending on whether they are paired or not, or if an entangled pair is owned by the same collector.

metadata.name: Grove #8
metadata.description:
A generative, impressionist painting of a small grove of trees in one of the four seasons. In spring and summer, flowers bloom in the meadow. A rare variation will create a charcoal drawing on white or black paper. Super rare will create a lighted winter scene that may have a moon behind the tree.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.

Press 's' to save a screenshot at any point. Image size is 1400x1082px.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution from 300 to 3,000 px.

On the paintings only, adding '&bg=true' will stop the painting after the background. Adding '&size=3000&bg=true' will give you a nice desktop background! 

Common Features:
- About 12-14 trees
- One of the four seasons
- One of 12 highlight color tints
- One of 12 shadow color tints
- Varying levels of distance haze
- Varying max brush sizes
- Varying amount of colors in the strokes

Less Common
- 15% chance of a charcoal drawing
- 50% chance it to be a dark winter scene

Rare
- Winter drawing with lights on the tree

Super Rare
- Winter drawing with a moon behind the tree

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #563
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. “The Bugged Tree”’s code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren’t under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there’s a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: 寧靜之海 Sea of ​​Tranquility #31
metadata.description:
我很愛看海，對我來說，它是可以讓我心靈平靜、靈感泉湧、包容我一切的存在。所以基於這個理由，我想讓大家都能擁有屬於自己獨一無二的海，希望你們在看這片海的時候也能因此獲得一些啟發。

這片海是由很多層浪組建而成，每個人的海浪層數和顏色都不太一樣（但仍然保持在一定範圍之間），這象徵沒有人的經歷能被別人取代；而天象則有三種，分別是太陽、月亮和星空。我將太陽營造出夸父追日、線條拖曳之感，月亮則是溫柔地散發光暈，星星則像活力滿滿的孩子在跳動一樣；海底的泡泡則是可以互動的，當滑鼠靠近，泡泡就會羞澀地躲開，你可以跟「她」玩捉迷藏。

以上是關於作品的一些背景跟內容介紹，希望所有鑄造作品的人都能喜歡這片深沉卻又不失斑斕的海洋。

I love watching the sea. For me, it is a place that can calm my mind, inspire me, and embrace everything about me. So for this reason, I want everyone to have their own unique sea, and I hope you can get some inspiration when looking at this sea.

This sea is made up of many layers of waves. The number and color of each person's waves are different (but still within a certain range), which symbolizes that no one's experience can be replaced by others; and the celestial phenomena are There are three types: the sun, the moon and the starry sky. I made the sun look like Kuafu chasing the sun, with lines dragging, the moon emits a gentle halo, and the stars jump like energetic children; the bubbles on the seabed are interactive, and when the mouse approaches , Bubble will shyly hide away, and you can play hide-and-seek with "her".

The above is some background and content introduction about the work. I hope that all those who created thｉｓ　ＮＦＴ will like this deep yet colorful ocean.

metadata.name: DRUNK... #6
metadata.description:
創作靈感源自於昨天，
或者該說是今天，
幫朋友慶生時放肆喝酒的心路歷程。
整個喝酒的過程，
就像是一場不停切換的旅程：一下清醒，一下暈眩，一下腦中東想西想。
最後，才終於意識到 —— I'm DRUNK...
但 DRUNK 之後又會是什麼心情呢? 
或許有人會感到難過，有人會覺得快樂，也有人只是放空。
至少對我來說，我是開心的！ 你呢?

ps.這段創作也是在我宿醉的情況下完成的 XD


The inspiration for this piece comes from yesterday—  
or perhaps I should say today—  
reflecting on the emotional journey of drinking recklessly while celebrating a friend’s birthday.  
The entire drinking experience felt like an ever-changing journey: moments of clarity, moments of dizziness, and moments where random thoughts filled my mind.  
Finally, it dawned on me — I’m DRUNK…  

But what comes after being drunk?  
Perhaps some might feel sad, others joyful, and some might just zone out.  
As for me, I was happy! How about you?  

P.S. This piece was also created while I was suffering from a hangover XD.

metadata.name: Tally! #5480
metadata.description:
Tally! Is a year long, free, open edition to celebrate fxhash v2. Data from the minting of Tally! will be used to create other new artworks.

This artwork is simply about counting up from one to wherever we end up, with a litle bit of Fizz Buzz thrown in. Mints that have a prime numbers* as factors will have slight variations. Sometimes those variations will combine, sometimes you have to get to really high numbers for multiple prime numbers to combine.

Where the finally Tally! ends up who knows? But there's going to be a lot of tallying along the way, and it'll give you something to do while waiting between other mints.

INSTRUCTIONS ::

'?forceWidth=xxxx' on the end of the URL to change the width of the image
's' = save image

attributes.name: Palette
attributes.value: Mall with too much sugar, reversed

metadata.name: Microgravity #939
metadata.description:
Microgravity is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Scale symmetry of abstract semiliquid forms.

Click on a section of the image to explore deeper.
- Use keys [0-9] to change the detail level.
- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "R" key to reset the coordinates.
